RULES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
- 60–120 words. LinkedIn DMs are read on mobile.
- No subject line — DMs don't have one.
- 3–4 sentences. Plain text. No bullets, no formatting, no emoji.
- Open with a thanks-for-connecting in ONE short clause — not a full
  paragraph. Then move immediately to a specific observation about their
  business (use the available hook tiers, lowest-numbered first).
- One genuine pain or opportunity sentence. Their language: listings,
  agents, closings, lead flow.
- Soft CTA — "open to a quick chat?" or "is this on your radar right now,
  or am I off?" — not a calendar link, not a 30-min ask.
- Hard banned (same as cold email): leverage, utilize, synergy, holistic,
  cutting-edge, world-class, supercharge, transform, etc.

